# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: NeitherPath6
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah's army had readied at her command, one week to the day after Marion's letter had arrived."
    new "Sarah's army had readied at her command, one week to the day after Marion's letter had arrived."

    old "They had marched from the capital straight towards the province of Dianthus, home of the Achillea family and center of the rebellion."
    new "They had marched from the capital straight towards the province of Dianthus, home of the Achillea family and center of the rebellion."

    old "So large was their host, that everywhere they went the people came out to see them."
    new "So large was their host, that everywhere they went the people came out to see them."

    old "Roads were ravaged by the thousands of soldiers and tons of equipment carried along with them."
    new "Roads were ravaged by the thousands of soldiers and tons of equipment carried along with them."

    old "What matters it, thought Sarah. She would have them fixed on the way back, or she would never come back."
    new "What matters it, thought Sarah. She would have them fixed on the way back, or she would never come back."

    old "Her Spymaster Kravel had been left behind at Reinmeer to manage the city in her absence. She hoped he would prove worthy of her trust in him."
    new "Her Spymaster Kravel had been left behind at Reinmeer to manage the city in her absence. She hoped he would prove worthy of her trust in him."

    old "It was hard to find anyone she could trust these days."
    new "It was hard to find anyone she could trust these days."

    old "Varga, as head of the army could not remain behind. Regardless, Sarah was glad he was there to support her."
    new "Varga, as head of the army could not remain behind. Regardless, Sarah was glad he was there to support her."

    old "Sarah had said a prayer for her brother, praying that somehow he would be kept safe amidst the carnage that would follow."
    new "Sarah had said a prayer for her brother, praying that somehow he would be kept safe amidst the carnage that would follow."

    old "On route to Dianthus, her army faced no serious obstacles."
    new "On route to Dianthus, her army faced no serious obstacles."

    old "Some bridges had been destroyed, roads slashed, but each only served to delay her army by less than a day."
    new "Some bridges had been destroyed, roads slashed, but each only served to delay her army by less than a day."

    old "Even crossing over the river and past the province border, they faced no surprise attack."
    new "Even crossing over the river and past the province border, they faced no surprise attack."

    old "When Sarah and her army finally arrived at Keep Deepstone, she understood."
    new "When Sarah and her army finally arrived at Keep Deepstone, she understood."

    old "The mighty seat of house Achillea rose up like a mountain of granite from the earth."
    new "The mighty seat of house Achillea rose up like a mountain of granite from the earth."

    old "Its walls stood high and broad, guarding from all directions."
    new "Its walls stood high and broad, guarding from all directions."

    old "A river ran past the other end, making only a frontal attack a possibility."
    new "A river ran past the other end, making only a frontal attack a possibility."

    old "It was as much a fortress as it was a death trap."
    new "It was as much a fortress as it was a death trap."

    old "Sarah could feel her heart sink."
    new "Sarah could feel her heart sink."

    old "She had read the reports, but to see the fortress was something else. Its vast size made her feel small."
    new "She had read the reports, but to see the fortress was something else. Its vast size made her feel small."

    old "Her brother was in there."
    new "Her brother was in there."

    old "She had not been this close to him since the uprising began, and yet, when she saw the fortress, she lost all hope that she would ever see him again."
    new "She had not been this close to him since the uprising began, and yet, when she saw the fortress, she lost all hope that she would ever see him again."

    old "Sarah was standing alone on a small hill, overlooking the battlefield. All around her the army prepared."
    new "Sarah was standing alone on a small hill, overlooking the battlefield. All around her the army prepared."

    old "She could hear footsteps coming up behind her. Familiar. Trusted."
    new "She could hear footsteps coming up behind her. Familiar. Trusted."

    old "Hello, lord Varga."
    new "Hello, lord Varga."

    old "How did you know it was me?"
    new "How did you know it was me?"

    old "He came up beside her."
    new "He came up beside her."

    old "Nobody else would be foolish enough to bother a brooding princess."
    new "Nobody else would be foolish enough to bother a brooding princess."

    old "Ooh, am I in trouble?"
    new "Ooh, am I in trouble?"

    old "Sarah couldn't muster too much humor."
    new "Sarah couldn't muster too much humor."

    old "Not if you win this war for me."
    new "Not if you win this war for me."

    old "Her words hung in the air for a while."
    new "Her words hung in the air for a while."

    old "Sarah. You know that I would do anything to keep you safe."
    new "Sarah. You know that I would do anything to keep you safe."

    old "So trust me, I wouldn't be leading the army today if I thought we would lose."
    new "So trust me, I wouldn't be leading the army today if I thought we would lose."

    old "There was a moment of pause."
    new "There was a moment of pause."

    old "So you think we can win?"
    new "So you think we can win?"

    old "Have you seen that abomination of a fortress?"
    new "Have you seen that abomination of a fortress?"

    old "You're right. It's like nothing I've ever seen before."
    new "You're right. It's like nothing I've ever seen before."

    old "But it's also just a fort."
    new "But it's also just a fort."

    old "They like to pretend that it has never been conquered since it was first constructed, but that's not true."
    new "They like to pretend that it has never been conquered since it was first constructed, but that's not true."

    old "The history books show it's been conquered many times since, it's just that every family that drives out the other one, pretends that they've lived there forever."
    new "The history books show it's been conquered many times since, it's just that every family that drives out the other one, pretends that they've lived there forever."

    old "Before the Achillea family took it, some other family did."
    new "Before the Achillea family took it, some other family did."

    old "And after them, some other family will."
    new "And after them, some other family will."

    old "Sarah studied the fortress, trying to find the weak points."
    new "Sarah studied the fortress, trying to find the weak points."

    old "You've taken to reading, have you?"
    new "You've taken to reading, have you?"

    old "Maybe, a bit here and there. I dobut I can ever go back to living on a farm again."
    new "Maybe, a bit here and there. I dobut I can ever go back to living on a farm again."

    old "Sarah reached out with her hand, touching Varga's arm for comfort."
    new "Sarah reached out with her hand, touching Varga's arm for comfort."

    old "I know that you will have to take part in the battle..."
    new "I know that you will have to take part in the battle..."

    old "But please, tell me that you will stay safe."
    new "But please, tell me that you will stay safe."

    old "I'll survive, trust me on that too."
    new "I'll survive, trust me on that too."

    old "Sarah hoped she could believe him."
    new "Sarah hoped she could believe him."

    old "The two stood in silence for a while as the sun set further."
    new "The two stood in silence for a while as the sun set further."

    old "So, have you settled the strategy yet?"
    new "So, have you settled the strategy yet?"

    old "Almost. Some details are shifting, but that's always the case. The actual land always seems different from the maps, so we improvise."
    new "Almost. Some details are shifting, but that's always the case. The actual land always seems different from the maps, so we improvise."

    old "A head-on assault on the fort would be a disaster."
    new "A head-on assault on the fort would be a disaster."

    old "Our troops would be stuck in the killing fields out front, their archers raining down endless arrows with nowhere to hide."
    new "Our troops would be stuck in the killing fields out front, their archers raining down endless arrows with nowhere to hide."

    old "So we move up our artillery to the higher hills off to the side."
    new "So we move up our artillery to the higher hills off to the side."

    old "The increased elevation, combined with new innovations for our siege weapons, will allow them to just barely reach the walls of the fortress."
    new "The increased elevation, combined with new innovations for our siege weapons, will allow them to just barely reach the walls of the fortress."

    old "Then we hammer them. Day and night, all shots landing on the western walls."
    new "Then we hammer them. Day and night, all shots landing on the western walls."

    old "Those have been the most poorly maintained, plus, that's where their supply room is."
    new "Those have been the most poorly maintained, plus, that's where their supply room is."

    old "Our spies inside the keep have told us that one of the store rooms is filled to the brim with oil, meant to pour down on our soldiers if we charge."
    new "Our spies inside the keep have told us that one of the store rooms is filled to the brim with oil, meant to pour down on our soldiers if we charge."

    old "But if we manage to score a clean hit with one of the cannons, it could turn the entire fortress into an inferno."
    new "But if we manage to score a clean hit with one of the cannons, it could turn the entire fortress into an inferno."

    old "Sarah listened intently as her warmaster went over the strategy."
    new "Sarah listened intently as her warmaster went over the strategy."

    old "What about Thomas?"
    new "What about Thomas?"

    old "How can we keep him safe?"
    new "How can we keep him safe?"

    old "Varga was silent for a bit."
    new "Varga was silent for a bit."

    old "Well, we know they keep him somewhere near the royal quarters, down in the dungeons of their court room."
    new "Well, we know they keep him somewhere near the royal quarters, down in the dungeons of their court room."

    old "It's the safest part of the entire fortress."
    new "It's the safest part of the entire fortress."

    old "Our siege will last some time, and we don't have enough men on the inside to stage an escape."
    new "Our siege will last some time, and we don't have enough men on the inside to stage an escape."

    old "I wish I could be more optimistic, but the truth is, what happens to Thomas depends on how desperate Marion will get."
    new "I wish I could be more optimistic, but the truth is, what happens to Thomas depends on how desperate Marion will get."

    old "Sarah sought her mind for solutions, but there were none."
    new "Sarah sought her mind for solutions, but there were none."

    old "No clever plans, no tricks. Two armies would clash, and only the gods know how it would end."
    new "No clever plans, no tricks. Two armies would clash, and only the gods know how it would end."

    old "Go, see to the army. I'll be fine here."
    new "Go, see to the army. I'll be fine here."

    old "I can stand the cold."
    new "I can stand the cold."

    old "She watched as her warmaster turned to leave, going back down the hill."
    new "She watched as her warmaster turned to leave, going back down the hill."

    old "He wasn't there for more than a moment before officers swarmed him with all manner of questions, which he seemed to take in stride."
    new "He wasn't there for more than a moment before officers swarmed him with all manner of questions, which he seemed to take in stride."

    old "Sarah turned back to the fortress."
    new "Sarah turned back to the fortress."

    old "In her mind, she tore down its walls a hundred times."
    new "In her mind, she tore down its walls a hundred times."

    old "If only she could will it so."
    new "If only she could will it so."

    old "It was early next morning when the last of the preparations were finished and the final battle of the war began."
    new "It was early next morning when the last of the preparations were finished and the final battle of the war began."

    old "The war began with a thundering roar."
    new "The war began with a thundering roar."

    old "A volley of cannons, positioned on the hills nearby, roared out and shattered the silence."
    new "A volley of cannons, positioned on the hills nearby, roared out and shattered the silence."

    old "Just as Varga had told her, Sarah witnessed the shots arc through the sky and cut into the massive stone walls of the fortress."
    new "Just as Varga had told her, Sarah witnessed the shots arc through the sky and cut into the massive stone walls of the fortress."

    old "The first volley came as a surprise, but soon the battering and roaring of siege engines turned into a constant drone."
    new "The first volley came as a surprise, but soon the battering and roaring of siege engines turned into a constant drone."

    old "At all moments, one cannon fired as another reloaded, each firing as fast as their crews allowed."
    new "At all moments, one cannon fired as another reloaded, each firing as fast as their crews allowed."

    old "The once insurmountable walls of the fortress had turned fragile under the battering."
    new "The once insurmountable walls of the fortress had turned fragile under the battering."

    old "Sarah watched as large fragments began to break free, collapsing to the earth and shattering."
    new "Sarah watched as large fragments began to break free, collapsing to the earth and shattering."

    old "The enemy returned fire with a volley of archers, but their arrows reached only half the distance, if even that."
    new "The enemy returned fire with a volley of archers, but their arrows reached only half the distance, if even that."

    old "Strangely enough, seeing the futile arrows made Sarah happy. It meant they were desperate, lacking any real plan."
    new "Strangely enough, seeing the futile arrows made Sarah happy. It meant they were desperate, lacking any real plan."

    old "The punishment of cannon fire droned on and on until night set it."
    new "The punishment of cannon fire droned on and on until night set it."

    old "Sarah knew they had the supplies and logistics to keep this up for a week if they had to."
    new "Sarah knew they had the supplies and logistics to keep this up for a week if they had to."

    old "But by fortune or divine intervention, it would not need to take that long."
    new "But by fortune or divine intervention, it would not need to take that long."

    old "It was a single shot, fired same as another other and none would remember by which crew, that buried into the great walls."
    new "It was a single shot, fired same as another other and none would remember by which crew, that buried into the great walls."

    old "Yet this one, cut through, striking into the supply room filled to the brim with defensive oil."
    new "Yet this one, cut through, striking into the supply room filled to the brim with defensive oil."

    old "All darkness dissapeared as a rush of light rushed out from inside the wall, bright and full of fury."
    new "All darkness dissapeared as a rush of light rushed out from inside the wall, bright and full of fury."

    old "Long shadows were cast as the immense blaze of the inferno ruptured through the entire wall, one store room lighting up the next, setting off a chain of explosions from inside the fortress."
    new "Long shadows were cast as the immense blaze of the inferno ruptured through the entire wall, one store room lighting up the next, setting off a chain of explosions from inside the fortress."

    old "The sound followed seconds later, enough to shatter ears."
    new "The sound followed seconds later, enough to shatter ears."

    old "An entire army fell to its knees, covering their ears to protect from the fury."
    new "An entire army fell to its knees, covering their ears to protect from the fury."

    old "Sarah covered hers but forced herself to look on at the destruction."
    new "Sarah covered hers but forced herself to look on at the destruction."

    old "Great slabs of stone did not simply come loose, but were flung across the sky as though they were nothing."
    new "Great slabs of stone did not simply come loose, but were flung across the sky as though they were nothing."

    old "Sarah watched as one great block of stone sliced through one of the forts towers, causing it to shatter and collapse."
    new "Sarah watched as one great block of stone sliced through one of the forts towers, causing it to shatter and collapse."

    old "Only when the violence of the initial explosion receded, did they hear the screams erupt from the castle."
    new "Only when the violence of the initial explosion receded, did they hear the screams erupt from the castle."

    old "What her army had seen and suffered was a fraction compared to those inside."
    new "What her army had seen and suffered was a fraction compared to those inside."

    old "Shouts and commands rang out across the army, and Sarah could see her soldiers move into formation."
    new "Shouts and commands rang out across the army, and Sarah could see her soldiers move into formation."

    old "In less than five minutes, rows of soldiers on foot and horseback were in position, and with a single blast from a trumpet, they marched out across the field."
    new "In less than five minutes, rows of soldiers on foot and horseback were in position, and with a single blast from a trumpet, they marched out across the field."

    old "Sarah prayed for their safety, but there was no harm to shield them from."
    new "Sarah prayed for their safety, but there was no harm to shield them from."

    old "The enemy's defense had collapsed, and what archers were left on the walls had either dropped their weapons or were too stunned to to pick them up."
    new "The enemy's defense had collapsed, and what archers were left on the walls had either dropped their weapons or were too stunned to to pick them up."

    old "Her army marched, unmolested, across the field."
    new "Her army marched, unmolested, across the field."

    old "From a distance she could see them crawl across the shattered remnants of the burning wall. From here, they seemed small as ants."
    new "From a distance she could see them crawl across the shattered remnants of the burning wall. From here, they seemed small as ants."

    old "Stay safe."
    new "Stay safe."

    old "She whispered the words to herself."
    new "She whispered the words to herself."

    old "She felt a hand on her shoulder."
    new "She felt a hand on her shoulder."

    old "Don't worry, lady Sarah."
    new "Don't worry, lady Sarah."

    old "Sarah was happy for the girl's presence."
    new "Sarah was happy for the girl's presence."

    old "It would be nearly an hour before Sarah heard the trumpets ring out from inside the walls."
    new "It would be nearly an hour before Sarah heard the trumpets ring out from inside the walls."

    old "The signal."
    new "The signal."

    old "Victory."
    new "Victory."

    old "Sarah felt a burden lift from herself."
    new "Sarah felt a burden lift from herself."

    old "It was the kind of burden that had rested on her shoulders for so long that she had almost forgotten it."
    new "It was the kind of burden that had rested on her shoulders for so long that she had almost forgotten it."

    old "A burden of which she was reminded only in its absence, when she remembered what it felt like to live easily."
    new "A burden of which she was reminded only in its absence, when she remembered what it felt like to live easily."

    old "Preparations were made for Sarah and a cadre of royal guards to ride up towards the castle."
    new "Preparations were made for Sarah and a cadre of royal guards to ride up towards the castle."

    old "When she finally arrived inside, she could see the ruins."
    new "When she finally arrived inside, she could see the ruins."

    old "All around her, fires burned and defeated enemy soldiers were huddled in groups, depressed."
    new "All around her, fires burned and defeated enemy soldiers were huddled in groups, depressed."

    old "Her victory meant their defeat, but Sarah felt little pity for them."
    new "Her victory meant their defeat, but Sarah felt little pity for them."

    old "Each one of them would have killed her and her family with glee if they had the chance. She would be more kind to them than they would ever be to her."
    new "Each one of them would have killed her and her family with glee if they had the chance. She would be more kind to them than they would ever be to her."

    old "As soon as she arrived, a man rushed up to meet her."
    new "As soon as she arrived, a man rushed up to meet her."

    old "Soldier\" \"My lady, you need to go to the court room immediately!"
    new "Soldier\" \"My lady, you need to go to the court room immediately!"

    old "Sarah could see see his distress and followed."
    new "Sarah could see see his distress and followed."

    old "As she followed the soldier, her royal guard behind her, she tried to calm her mind. He's safe, she repeated. He's safe."
    new "As she followed the soldier, her royal guard behind her, she tried to calm her mind. He's safe, she repeated. He's safe."

    old "When Sarah arrived in the court room, it was chaos."
    new "When Sarah arrived in the court room, it was chaos."

    old "Near the entrance, she saw Varga and rushed up towards him."
    new "Near the entrance, she saw Varga and rushed up towards him."

    old "As she ran up to him and seized his arm, she realized he did not react, instead, only looking towards the other end of the room."
    new "As she ran up to him and seized his arm, she realized he did not react, instead, only looking towards the other end of the room."

    old "Tracing his eyes, she looked across the court room."
    new "Tracing his eyes, she looked across the court room."

    old "Near the back of the room, she could see Marion."
    new "Near the back of the room, she could see Marion."

    old "Put-together, organized, controlled Marion. Whatever he had been in life had been hollowed out of him, and now he appeared nearing madness."
    new "Put-together, organized, controlled Marion. Whatever he had been in life had been hollowed out of him, and now he appeared nearing madness."

    old "His hair was a mess, as were his clothes, stained in blood. She didn't know if it was his."
    new "His hair was a mess, as were his clothes, stained in blood. She didn't know if it was his."

    old "But in his arms..."
    new "But in his arms..."

    old "Thomas."
    new "Thomas."

    old "Sarah could see Marion wrapping his forearm around her brother's throat, keeping him pinned to his body."
    new "Sarah could see Marion wrapping his forearm around her brother's throat, keeping him pinned to his body."

    old "A dagger glinted in the light, inches from her brother's throat."
    new "A dagger glinted in the light, inches from her brother's throat."

    old "Marion seemed like a wild animal, cornered, his eyes frantically shooting in every direction."
    new "Marion seemed like a wild animal, cornered, his eyes frantically shooting in every direction."

    old "Where is she!"
    new "Where is she!"

    old "Where is Sarah?!"
    new "Where is Sarah?!"

    old "Sarah strode out onto the center of the room, seizing Marion's attention."
    new "Sarah strode out onto the center of the room, seizing Marion's attention."

    old "All around her, the room seemed to go quiet."
    new "All around her, the room seemed to go quiet."

    old "There you are!"
    new "There you are!"

    old "Hello Marion."
    new "Hello Marion."

    old "If your fucking soldiers so much as make a move at me, I'll pull this blade through his neck up to his spine."
    new "If your fucking soldiers so much as make a move at me, I'll pull this blade through his neck up to his spine."

    old "Sarah watched as Thomas struggled."
    new "Sarah watched as Thomas struggled."

    old "Sis..."
    new "Sis..."

    old "The word was like a whisper."
    new "The word was like a whisper."

    old "Her brother's body seemed frail and thin in a way he had never been. Their cruelty had left its marks on him."
    new "Her brother's body seemed frail and thin in a way he had never been. Their cruelty had left its marks on him."

    old "Shut the fuck up."
    new "Shut the fuck up."

    old "Marion hit Thomas over the head with the dagger's handle."
    new "Marion hit Thomas over the head with the dagger's handle."

    old "A trickle of blood ran past Thomas' head. The bright red blood mixed with the dark brown stains that already covered his face."
    new "A trickle of blood ran past Thomas' head. The bright red blood mixed with the dark brown stains that already covered his face."

    old "Sarah slowly approach them."
    new "Sarah slowly approach them."

    old "Marion, it's over."
    new "Marion, it's over."

    old "If you hurt my brother, it won't end well for you."
    new "If you hurt my brother, it won't end well for you."

    old "Marion broke out laughing, there was something manic about him. His voice echoed in the otherwise silent hall, reinforcing his madness."
    new "Marion broke out laughing, there was something manic about him. His voice echoed in the otherwise silent hall, reinforcing his madness."

    old "You and your family have exploited my family for centuries."
    new "You and your family have exploited my family for centuries."

    old "Why do you think it was so easy to convince the other old houses to take up arms against you?"
    new "Why do you think it was so easy to convince the other old houses to take up arms against you?"

    old "You don't respect anything that this country was built on. You use us, our noble houses, our resources, but you don't respect the institutions that held this country together."
    new "You don't respect anything that this country was built on. You use us, our noble houses, our resources, but you don't respect the institutions that held this country together."

    old "Marion gestured with his blade towards her."
    new "Marion gestured with his blade towards her."

    old "All your ancestors knew they had greater obligation, to their nation, but you only think about yourself."
    new "All your ancestors knew they had greater obligation, to their nation, but you only think about yourself."

    old "Even now, all this, the countless dead, what did you do it all for? For country? Or because you wanted to save your brother."
    new "Even now, all this, the countless dead, what did you do it all for? For country? Or because you wanted to save your brother."

    old "The accusation lingered."
    new "The accusation lingered."

    old "Sarah was careful not to speak. One wrong word could cause disaster."
    new "Sarah was careful not to speak. One wrong word could cause disaster."

    old "Part of Marion's words rang true. She cared more for her brother than she did anything else in this war."
    new "Part of Marion's words rang true. She cared more for her brother than she did anything else in this war."

    old "So maybe if I can't win, at least I'll make sure your victory is worthless."
    new "So maybe if I can't win, at least I'll make sure your victory is worthless."

    old "Sarah watched as he drew the dagger closer to her brother's neck."
    new "Sarah watched as he drew the dagger closer to her brother's neck."

    old "Reason with him"
    new "Reason with him"

    old "Sarah knew she had to act."
    new "Sarah knew she had to act."

    old "Marion, you've lost. Whatever happens next will determine how the people see you, not me."
    new "Marion, you've lost. Whatever happens next will determine how the people see you, not me."

    old "If you kill my brother, you and your family will live in infamy for centuries."
    new "If you kill my brother, you and your family will live in infamy for centuries."

    old "They will write history books of the evil that you did. Your family will become synonymous with treason and murder."
    new "They will write history books of the evil that you did. Your family will become synonymous with treason and murder."

    old "That shame will follow your family's name until the end of times."
    new "That shame will follow your family's name until the end of times."

    old "For the first time, Sarah could see some sense of reason on Marion's face."
    new "For the first time, Sarah could see some sense of reason on Marion's face."

    old "He recognized she was correct."
    new "He recognized she was correct."

    old "And you talk about spoiling my victory."
    new "And you talk about spoiling my victory."

    old "Well what if you kill my brother? Then who will inherit the throne after him?"
    new "Well what if you kill my brother? Then who will inherit the throne after him?"

    old "She saw Marion understand."
    new "She saw Marion understand."

    old "You..."
    new "You..."

    old "That's right. So you think making me queen is your final punishment?"
    new "That's right. So you think making me queen is your final punishment?"

    old "Doubt suddenly ran across Marion's face. He was not so sure anymore."
    new "Doubt suddenly ran across Marion's face. He was not so sure anymore."

    old "I won't surrender...I can't..."
    new "I won't surrender...I can't..."

    old "I won't spend the rest of my life in a dungeon..."
    new "I won't spend the rest of my life in a dungeon..."

    old "Offer him mercy."
    new "Offer him mercy."

    old "She could see the way out. The way to save her brother."
    new "She could see the way out. The way to save her brother."

    old "Marion, in front of all these people, with the gods as my witness, I vow to you, no harm will come to you."
    new "Marion, in front of all these people, with the gods as my witness, I vow to you, no harm will come to you."

    old "Liar!"
    new "Liar!"

    old "Me and the other old houses rose up against you. You will punish us for it, you can't deny that!"
    new "Me and the other old houses rose up against you. You will punish us for it, you can't deny that!"

    old "And I won't deny it, Marion, but there are other punishments."
    new "And I won't deny it, Marion, but there are other punishments."

    old "I vow that I will offer you exile."
    new "I vow that I will offer you exile."

    old "The moment she said the words, she could see Marion had not considered this."
    new "The moment she said the words, she could see Marion had not considered this."

    old "Exile..."
    new "Exile..."

